Tolerate SCSI hosts that cannot accept ALPM policy writes.

Two real-world cases break profile application because `?` propagates
the first sysfs write error and aborts the loop:

  * USB-attached SCSI, virtio-scsi, software RAID, and card readers
    appear under /sys/class/scsi_host/ but expose no ALPM attribute,
    so the write returns ENOENT.
  * AHCI ports whose BIOS keeps ALPM under firmware control read
    "keep_firmware_settings" and reject writes with EOPNOTSUPP (errno
    95); e.g. the Clevo P95xEx / System76 oryp4.

Both are "this host cannot be configured via ALPM, skip it" cases. The
rest of the profile (CPU governor, pstate, PCI runtime-PM) already
applies even when this step fails, but the daemon keeps reporting the
previous profile and the CLI exits non-zero.

Upstream: https://github.com/pop-os/system76-power/issues/377

--- a/src/daemon/profiles.rs
+++ b/src/daemon/profiles.rs
@@ -205,9 +205,30 @@ fn scsi_host_link_time_pm_policy(policies: &'static [&'static str]) -> Result<()
     for device in ScsiHost::iter() {
         match device {
             Ok(device) => {
-                device.set_link_power_management_policy(policies).map_err(|why| {
-                    ScsiHostError::LinkTimePolicy(policies[0], device.id().to_owned(), why)
-                })?;
+                // Skip hosts without an ALPM attribute (USB-attached SCSI,
+                // virtio-scsi, software RAID, card readers, etc.).
+                if !device.path().join("link_power_management_policy").exists() {
+                    continue;
+                }
+                if let Err(why) = device.set_link_power_management_policy(policies) {
+                    // Tolerate hosts that cannot accept policy changes: ENOENT
+                    // on hot-remove races, and EOPNOTSUPP on firmware-locked
+                    // AHCI ports (link_power_management_policy reads
+                    // "keep_firmware_settings").
+                    match why.kind() {
+                        io::ErrorKind::NotFound | io::ErrorKind::Unsupported => {
+                            log::debug!(
+                                "skipping SCSI host {}: ALPM unwritable ({})",
+                                device.id(), why
+                            );
+                        }
+                        _ => {
+                            return Err(ScsiHostError::LinkTimePolicy(
+                                policies[0], device.id().to_owned(), why,
+                            ));
+                        }
+                    }
+                }
             }
             Err(why) => {
                 log::warn!("failed to iterate SCSI Host device: {}", why);
